.TH FONT(1),User Commands,FONT(1)

.SH NAME
font - load a Unifont-derived 8x16 text-mode font

.SH SYNOPSIS
font

.SH DESCRIPTION
font switches the console into 80x30 text mode and uploads an 8x16 glyph set derived from GNU Unifont into VERA tile memory.
After font completes, subsequent text output uses the new glyphs until the display mode is changed again.

font locks the VERA registers for the duration of the upload and restores them before exiting.
It takes no options or arguments.

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: Font loaded successfully.

1: Failed to acquire the VERA register lock.
